.SH NAME
.PP
envctl-identity-export - Export identity for backup


.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBenvctl identity export [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Export your identity as a paper backup using recovery words.

.PP
The recovery words can be used to restore your identity on a new machine.
Store them securely - anyone with these words can become you.

.PP
Examples:
  envctl identity export --paper
  envctl identity export --paper --plain
  envctl identity export --paper --qr
  envctl identity export --paper --output backup.txt


.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for export

.PP
\fB--output\fP=""
	write to file instead of stdout

.PP
\fB--paper\fP[=false]
	export as paper backup (mnemonic words)

.PP
\fB--plain\fP[=false]
	plain text output (no box)

.PP
\fB--qr\fP[=false]
	display as QR code


